      "message": "I initially thought this was a good idea, but looking at the code now, I\u0027m not sure (unless something else changes). Currently, because of ownership/lifetime, the only thing that can really be cached for repeated application is an SkSL::Interpreter object (dynamically stored via std::unique_ptr\u003cSkSL::Interpreter\u003e, most likely).\n\nBut if you do that, you now need to re-create the interpreter to run the compiled code with different inputs.\n\nI think that either inputs needs to be supplied to run(), or Interpreter should be a short-lived stack object that doesn\u0027t assume ownershop of the program and byte code?",
